This paper is about video captioning, which involves computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes improvements to the existing models, which involves machine learning techniques such as recurrent neural networks and loss functions, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper deals with video data, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper utilizes semantic information to improve the performance of the model, which involves artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category.
